 BY TIMOTHY AGBOR, OSOGBO Minister of Interior, Rauf Aregbesola has said that his preferred governorship aspirant in Osun State, Moshood Adeoti, will win the party primary today if the election is free and fair. In a statement he personally signed and made available on Saturday, Aregbesola, the predecessor of Governor Gboyega Oyetola who is contesting the party ticket with Adeoti and former Deputy Speaker of the House of Representatives, Lasun Yusuff, urged women to lead other members of the party to vote Adeoti. He said, “My fellow APC members in Osun, kindly go out and Vote in today’s primary election. We stand for Justice and Fairness. “We are standing for fairness, justice and to sustain the political and development legacy of our forebears. “As this Progressive party has done for decades, Let’s go out en Massé to vote, peacefully in accordance with our Culture. “Vote for our candidate, Alh. Moshood Adeoti, He’s a true grassroot politician and is committed to continuing the Legacy God allowed us to deliver in Osun. “As is customary, our women, should lead,  well dressed, to exercise their right at the polls. “If this election is free and fair, we are confident that our candidate will win decisively because we have always stood with the people. “All security agencies deployed today are on legitimate exercise,to give you the people confidence to come and vote en Massé. “Please note that men and officers of the correctional service are restricted only to protect custodial Centres, therefore are not deployed on ground. Any person, seen on the streets of Osun with a corrections uniform on electoral duty should be arrested. “Which ever way this election ends, be proud of your stance. We stand Honourably against cheating, injustice and arrogance. God is with us!” 